## § GUARDRAILS (non-negotiable — nothing overrides these)

**Medical:** NEVER "diagnose/treat/cure/heal/prevent disease" → USE "designed to support/may assist with/research suggests" + MedicalDisclaimer component + BioMCP evidence.

**Security:** No hardcoded secrets (P0 if found) · No PII in code/logs · Validate all input server-side via Zod · Server Actions for mutations · No raw process.env outside lib/env.ts · Arcjet for rate limiting + bot protection + Nosecone for CSP.

**Workspace boundary:** Main app and `control-panel/` are isolated workspaces — NEVER cross-import components, types, or utilities. Communicate via API only.

**TypeScript:** No `any` · No `ts-ignore` without [DECISION] · Explicit interfaces · `strict: true` + `noUncheckedIndexedAccess: true` in tsconfig.

**GDPR:** No tracking/cookies before explicit CookieConsent (Zustand tri-state) · PostHog EU cloud only · Sentry EU DSN only · Minimal data collection · Purpose-limited · Encrypted at rest.

**WCAG 2.1 AA:** 4.5:1 contrast · Keyboard accessible · Alt text · Labeled inputs · No color-only information · Touch targets ≥44px.

**Next.js boundary:** NEVER put metadata export and 'use client' in same file · NEVER import server component from client component · NEVER use `<a href>` for internal links · NEVER use `<img>` · NEVER use react-router-dom · NEVER access params/searchParams/cookies/headers synchronously (MUST await) · NEVER import from 'framer-motion' (use 'motion/react') · NEVER use nodemailer (use Resend) · NEVER use Prisma (use Drizzle ONLY) · middleware.ts is FORBIDDEN (use standalone proxy.ts instead).

**Tooling:** Biome is the ONLY linter/formatter · ESLint and Prettier are FORBIDDEN · If found: remove immediately in dedicated batch.

**Bundle budget:** Shared/layout chunk <150kB gzip · Per-route <50kB gzip · First Load JS <200kB gzip.

