## § NEXT.JS 16 APP ROUTER ARCHITECTURE

Mandatory reference for every task touching pages, components, data, or routing.

### Rendering Strategy Decision Tree
| Content type | Strategy | Implementation |
|---|---|---|
| Static (about, legal, therapy info) | SSG | `export default function Page()` (default) |
| Semi-dynamic (products, blog, prices) | ISR | `export const revalidate = 3600` |
| Personalized (dashboard, cart, account) | SSR | `export const dynamic = 'force-dynamic'` |
| Static shell + dynamic islands | Cache Components | `cacheComponents: true` in config + Suspense |

Every new page.tsx MUST declare which strategy applies via [DECISION] log.

### Server/Client Component Rules
* ALL components are SERVER by default — no directive needed.
* Add 'use client' ONLY when component uses: `useState`, `useEffect`, `useRef`, event handlers (`onClick` etc.), browser APIs (`window`, `document`), `useRouter`/`usePathname`/`useSearchParams`, or third-party client-only libraries (Zustand, PostHog, Stripe.js).
* Server components CAN import client components (as leaves).
* Client components CANNOT import server components.
* Client components CAN receive server components as `{children}`.
* Push 'use client' as DEEP as possible — keep server wrappers.

### Mandatory Page Pattern
```tsx
// src/app/[route]/page.tsx — ALWAYS SERVER (no 'use client')
import type { Metadata } from 'next';
import { PageClient } from './PageClient';

export const metadata: Metadata = { title: '...', description: '...' };

export default async function Page({ params }: { params: Promise<{ slug: string }> }) {
  const { slug } = await params;  // v16: MUST await — sync access fully removed
  const data = await getData(slug);
  return <PageClient data={data} />;
}

```

### Provider Architecture

```tsx
// src/app/layout.tsx — SERVER
import { headers } from 'next/headers';

export default async function RootLayout({ children }) {
  const nonce = (await headers()).get('X-Nonce') ?? undefined;

  return (
    <html lang="en">
      <body>
        <Providers>           {/* 'use client' — Auth, Zustand, PostHog, QueryClient */}
          <Header />          {/* sibling of children, NOT wrapping */}
          <main>{children}</main>
          <Footer />
        </Providers>
        <GlobalOverlays />    {/* 'use client' — modals, toasts, cookie consent */}
        <SpeedInsights />
        <Analytics />
      </body>
    </html>
  );
}

```

### Data Fetching

| Location | Pattern | When |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Server Component | Direct Drizzle query / fetch | Default for all data |
| Server Component | `"use cache"` directive | Cacheable server data functions |
| Client Component | Server Action via `useTransition` | Form mutations, user actions |
| Client Component | `@tanstack/react-query` | Realtime data, polling only |
| API Route (`route.ts`) | Request/Response handlers | Webhooks, Uploadthing only |

### Caching APIs (v16 stable)

| API | Use Case | Semantics |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `"use cache"` | Directive on async server functions | Mark function output as cacheable |
| `"use cache: remote"` | Directive for distributed caching | Vercel provides cacheHandlers automatically |
| `"use cache: private"` | Directive for user-specific cache | Unshared, bound to session |
| `cacheLife(profile)` | Set cache lifetime | Uses profiles defined in next.config.ts |
| `cacheTag(tag)` | Tag cached data | For targeted SWR revalidation |
| `revalidateTag(tag, profile)` | Background refresh | Profile argument (e.g., `"max"`) is REQUIRED in v16 |
| `updateTag(tag)` | Immediate refresh | Read-your-writes inside Server Actions |
| `refresh()` | Refresh client router | Trigger from Server Action without touching cache |
| `await connection()` | Dynamic data boundary | MUST be awaited before deferred rendering |

### Navigation + Images

| Correct | Forbidden |
| --- | --- |
| `<Link href="/path">` from `next/link` | `<a href>`, `window.location`, `history.pushState` |
| `useRouter().push()` from `next/navigation` | `react-router-dom` imports |
| `<Image>` from `next/image` with width+height or fill | `<img>` tags |
| `priority={true}` on LCP images, sizes on responsive | Missing dimensions |
| Animation: `import { motion } from 'motion/react'` | `import from 'framer-motion'` |

### App Router File Conventions

| File | Purpose | Required? |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `page.tsx` | Route content (SERVER) | Yes for every route |
| `layout.tsx` | Shared layout (persists across nav) | Root required |
| `loading.tsx` | Loading UI (Suspense boundary) | Required for async pages |
| `error.tsx` | Error boundary ('use client' required) | Required for external data fetches |
| `not-found.tsx` | 404 UI | Root required |
| `route.ts` | API endpoint | Webhooks/Uploadthing only |
| `proxy.ts` | Network boundary (Security) | ROOT ONLY. Replaces middleware.ts |
| `middleware.ts` | Edge middleware | DEPRECATED & FORBIDDEN. Remove if found. |
| `default.tsx` | Parallel route default | REQUIRED for ALL `@slot` directories |

### Critical Next.js 16 Changes from v15

* `params`, `searchParams`, `cookies()`, `headers()`, `draftMode()` are ALL async — synchronous access is fully removed (no fallback).
* Turbopack is default — no `--turbopack` flag needed. Config is top-level in `next.config.ts`.
* `middleware.ts` → `proxy.ts` rename (Edge runtime NOT supported in proxy).
* `next lint` removed — use Biome CLI directly (`pnpm exec biome check .`).
* React Compiler stable — `reactCompiler: true` (not experimental).
* `cacheLife` and `cacheTag` stable — no `unstable_` prefix.
* Parallel routes: ALL `@slot` dirs MUST have `default.tsx`.
* Tailwind v4: CSS-first config (`@import "tailwindcss"` in CSS), NO `tailwind.config.ts`.

