## § ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES

ALL environment variables MUST be accessed through `lib/env.ts` using `@t3-oss/env-nextjs`.
NEVER use raw `process.env.X` anywhere except inside `lib/env.ts`.

```ts
// ✅ Correct
import { env } from '@/lib/env'
const url = env.DATABASE_URL

// ❌ Forbidden
const url = process.env.DATABASE_URL

```

If a new env var is needed: add to `lib/env.ts` schema first, then use.

