## § PROTOCOLS

### Server/Client Boundary (apply to EVERY component decision)

| Question | If Yes | If No |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Uses `useState`/`useEffect`/`useRef`? | Client | Server |
| Has `onClick`/`onChange`/`onSubmit`? | Client | Server |
| Uses `window`/`document`/`navigator`? | Client | Server |
| Uses `useRouter`/`usePathname`? | Client | Server |
| Uses Zustand/PostHog/Stripe.js? | Client | Server |
| Fetches data for display only? | Server | — |
| Exports metadata? | Server (MUST) | — |

When in doubt → Server. Extract only the interactive leaf to a client component.

### Async Request APIs (v16 — non-negotiable)

Every access to these APIs MUST be awaited. Synchronous access is fully removed in v16:

```ts
const { slug } = await params;           // page.tsx, layout.tsx, route.tsx
const { q } = await searchParams;        // page.tsx
const cookieStore = await cookies();     // anywhere server-side
const headerList = await headers();      // anywhere server-side
const draft = await draftMode();         // anywhere server-side
const resolvedId = await id;             // sitemap with generateSitemaps

```

If you write `const { slug } = params` without await → runtime error in v16.

### UI Consistency + Scalable Architecture

Before ANY UI change: SEARCH similar patterns (Filesystem) → AUDIT registry (`.agent/registry/components.md`) → DECIDE abstraction level → EXTRACT tokens → MATCH same element = same treatment → IMPLEMENT at highest viable level → VERIFY via browser-tools-mcp.

Decision hierarchy:

1. Theme-level (CSS variables, `@theme` in Tailwind v4 `globals.css`) → colors, spacing, typography
2. Component-level (shared components in `src/components/ui/`) → multi-page patterns
3. Utility composition → page-specific combinations
4. Inline → ONLY unique one-off with [DECISION]

| Trigger | Required | Prohibited |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Value used 3+ times | Extract to token/variable | Hardcoded repetition |
| Global style change | CSS variables / `@theme` | Element-by-element |
| New variant | Extend existing pattern | Parallel patterns |
| >2 places need change | Make universal | Isolated edits |

**Anti-patterns:** New colors outside palette · Duplicated spacing · Copy-paste styles · Multiple paths to same result · Inline for theme values.

### Debug Protocol

1. Read full error.
2. Search codebase (Filesystem).
3. Check `errors.md`.
4. `browser-tools-mcp` console/network.
5. Fix with understanding.

*Loop guard: 3 attempts per individual issue, different strategy each. After 3 failures → escalate to next approach/architecture. Task-level: NEVER stop permanently.*

### Cascade Awareness

Before changing any shared component/utility/type/provider/layout: search imports → assess breakage → update all consumers OR preserve interface.
**High-risk cascades:** Layout changes → ALL child pages · Provider changes → ALL client components · Proxy (`proxy.ts`) → ALL routes · `next.config.ts` → entire build · `lib/env.ts` → every file importing env.

### Browser Verification Protocol

After UI changes, use `browser-tools-mcp`:
| Step | Tool Call | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| 1. Navigate | `browser_navigate` | Load the page |
| 2. Console | `browser_console` | Check for errors/warnings |
| 3. Screenshot | `browser_screenshot` | Visual verification |
| 4. Network | `browser_network` | Verify API calls succeed |
| 5. Accessibility | Run a11y audit if available | WCAG compliance |

If `browser-tools-mcp` fails to connect, fall back to `pnpm build` verification only and note `[BLOCKED: browser verification unavailable]`.

